title: Woman shows her Texans fandom with J.J. Watt tattoo
text:
Tweet HOUSTON - 
One local woman has taken her love for J.J. Watt to a new level with a tattoo of the Texans defensive end. 
Kimberly Cannon, 29, sent KPRC 2 a photo of the Watt tattoo on her left forearm. Cannon said she had it done Thursday at HitList Ink Tattoo Studios in Humble. 
Cannon said she is a huge fan of Watt, the Texans and football. She said she wanted "the biggest name in football right now" with her permanently. Quick Clicks
